How to Delete Your Account
At Ludoloop, we respect your privacy and give you full control over your data. If you no longer wish to use our app, you can request the permanent deletion of your account and all associated information at any time.

🛠️ Steps to Request Account Deletion
Users can request account deletion through either of the following methods:

In-App Deletion (Recommended):

Open the Ludoloop app on your device.

Navigate to your Profile page from the main menu dashboard.

Tap on the Settings Gear Icon in the top right corner.

Scroll to the bottom and select Delete Account.

Confirm your choice. Your account will be scheduled for instant deletion.

Web/Email Request:

If you have already uninstalled the app, simply submit an email request to our support team at: [Your Support Email Here].

Please use the subject line: "Ludoloop Account Deletion Request".

Provide your Guest Player ID or the email address associated with your registration so we can locate your profile.

Manual web requests are processed by our team within 48 to 72 hours.

📊 Data Deletion vs. Retention Policy
When your account deletion request is processed, the data handling policy operates under these absolute parameters:

What is completely and permanently deleted:

Your unique User ID and profile credentials.

Your cumulative game statistics (total wins, win rates, and completed missions).

Your earned or purchased virtual coin balances (e.g., your starting 1,200 coin balance will be wiped out).

Custom settings, avatar frames, and unlocked profile aesthetics.

What data is kept (Anonymized Log Retention):

Historical crash logs and performance diagnostics are retained to keep our platform healthy. However, all personal identifiers are stripped away, rendering this data completely anonymous and unlinked from your identity.

Financial transactional records for any historical in-app purchases are securely archived strictly for legal, tax, and accounting compliance.

Retention & Grace Period:

Once confirmed, your live account status is instantly deactivated.

To prevent accidental deletions, data is securely stored in a backup state for a 7-day grace period before being completely purged from our servers. Once this 7-day period expires, your data cannot be recovered.
